{
    "name": "Steady Way",
    "description": "Learn what matters",
    "about": "A steady way is about moving forward with patience, consistency, and balance instead of rushing for quick results. It’s the idea of choosing sustainability over speed—making small but continuous progress every day that compounds into big achievements over time. A steady path also means being resilient; setbacks don’t derail you because your foundation is strong. It values clarity, discipline, and persistence, keeping you on track without constant distractions or drastic changes. In simple terms, a steady way is walking with purpose instead of sprinting and burning out—it might take longer, but it ensures you actually reach your destination."
}

